text.tspan: The four main actors are evident. According to the Single Responsibility Principle,
these four actors will be the four primary sources of change for the system. Every time
some new feature is added, or some existing feature is changed, that step will be taken
to serve one of these actors. Therefore we want to partition the system such that a
change to one actor does not affect any of the other actors.
